Tavatron whimpered softly, her internal repairs were slow due to the amount 
of damage she had recieved.

"That's probably best. I should be completely recovored in a few 
mega-cycles." Tavatron's optics were already half-closed, she opened her 
mouth in a long, wolfish yawn. She rested her head against Dinobot's 
shoulder, already half-asleep.

>* Dinobot let Tavatron lean against him and helped her walk towards the
>cliffs surrounding the valley, he knew that it would be painstakingly slow
>to get back to base.
>He looked at the cliffs ahead and sighed, they would be very difficult for 
>a
>wounded bot to climb.
>Dinobot stopped and looked around with his scanners, it wasn't long before
>he located a cave.*
>
>" It would be better if we stayed here until you have healed fully, there 
>is
>shelter 5 clicks from here."
>
>* Dinobot waited to see Tavatron's response*
